"The Law of Ueki (Japanese: \u3046\u3048\u304d\u306e\u6cd5\u5247, Hepburn: Ueki no H\u014dsoku) is a Japanese manga series written and illustrated by Tsubasa Fukuchi. It was serialized in Shogakukan's Weekly Sh\u014dnen Sunday from August 2001 to October 2004, with Its chapters collected in sixteen tank\u014dbon volumes. A manga sequel, The Law of Ueki Plus, was serialized in Weekly Sh\u014dnen Sunday from April 2005 to June 2007. It was licensed in North America for English language release by Viz Media. A 51-episode anime television series adaptation produced by Studio Deen was broadcast on TV Tokyo from April 2005 to March 2006. In North America, the series was first licensed by Geneon in 2005 and later by Discotek Media in 2018."